<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-732-471  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 732 471.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Industrial Engineering  Dec 1990 v22 n12 p16(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>AGVs are flexible and trainable. (automated guided vehicles)(material handling)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sims, Ralph Jr.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The need for automated, sometimes random, and quick responsehandling of high transaction rates are needed when flexiblemanufacturing systems and just-in-time operations and precisematerial management generate fluctuating volumes and varying flowpaths.andP;  A flexible small unit, computer compatible handling systemwith minimal labor content is then needed, such as the automatedguided vehicle (AGV).andP;  The AGV is used to serve as a tool loadingwork bench, transfer device, travelling tool holder and machineloading and unloading system in the development of the computerintegrated factory (CIM).andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Flexible Manufacturing SystemsJust In Time Inventory SystemsApplicationsProgrammableComputer-aided manufacturingMaterials handling.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>